#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1
msgid "Package Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:3
msgid ""
"moon uses a package file to identify and describe a package. The legacy "
"format is `moon.pkg.json`, and the new format is `moon.pkg`. For full "
"JSON schema, please check [moon's "
"repository](https://github.com/moonbitlang/moon/blob/main/crates/moonbuild/template/pkg.schema.json)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:7
msgid "New format (`moon.pkg`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:9
msgid ""
"The new format is a concise DSL. You can generate or reformat it from an "
"existing `moon.pkg.json` with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:12
msgid "moon fmt -C <module_dir>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:16 ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:263
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:18
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/language/packages/virtual\",\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"options(\n"
"  \"is-main\": true,\n"
"  overrides: [ \"moonbit-community/language/packages/implement\" ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:22
msgid ""
"In `moon.pkg`, dependencies are declared in an `import { ... }` block. "
"Use `@alias` to set a custom alias:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:25 ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:141
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgA\",\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgC\" @c,\n"
"  \"moonbitlang/core/builtin\",\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:29
msgid ""
"All other fields from `moon.pkg.json` move into a single `options(...)` "
"block. The key names and value shapes are unchanged; the legacy keys that"
" contain `-` must be quoted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:33
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"virtual\": { \"has-default\": true },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:37
msgid "The `moon.pkg` format allows comments `//...`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:39
msgid "Full syntax of `moon.pkg` is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:41
msgid ""
"moon_pkg ::= statement*\n"
"statement ::= import | assign | apply\n"
"\n"
"import ::= \"import\" \"{\" (import_item \",\")* import_item? \"}\" "
"import_kind?\n"
"import_item ::= STRING (\"@\" PKG_NAME)?\n"
"import_kind ::= \"for\" STRING\n"
"\n"
"assign ::= LIDENT \"=\" expr\n"
"\n"
"apply ::= LIDENT \"(\" (argument \",\")* argument? \")\"\n"
"argument ::= LIDENT \":\" expr | STRING \":\" expr  \n"
"\n"
"expr ::= array | object | apply | STRING | INT | \"true\" | \"false\"\n"
"array ::= \"[\" (expr \",\")* expr? \"]\"\n"
"object ::= \"{\" (field \",\")* field? \"}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:59
msgid "Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:61
msgid ""
"The package name is not configurable; it is determined by the directory "
"name of the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:63
msgid "Formatter"
msgstr "フォーマッタ"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:65
msgid ""
"The `formatter` field configures `moon fmt` for this package. Currently "
"it supports `ignore`, a list of file names that the formatter should "
"skip."
msgstr ""
"`formatter` フィールドは、このパッケージに対する `moon fmt` "
"の設定を行います。現在は、フォーマッタがスキップするファイル名の一覧である `ignore` をサポートしています。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:68
msgid ""
"This is useful for generated files or files that you intentionally keep "
"in a different format. Files produced by `pre-build` are already skipped "
"automatically, so `formatter.ignore` is mainly for additional files you "
"want to exclude."
msgstr ""
"これは、生成ファイルや、意図的に別の形式のままにしておきたいファイルに便利です。`pre-build` "
"で生成されたファイルはすでに自動でスキップされるため、`formatter.ignore` は主に追加で除外したいファイルのために使います。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md
msgid "moon.pkg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:77
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  formatter: {\n"
"    ignore: [ \"generated.mbt\", \"snapshot.mbt\" ],\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md
msgid "moon.pkg.json"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:88
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"formatter\": {\n"
"    \"ignore\": [\"generated.mbt\", \"snapshot.mbt\"]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:99
msgid "is-main"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:101
msgid ""
"The `is-main` field is used to specify whether a package needs to be "
"linked into an executable file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:103
msgid ""
"The output of the linking process depends on the backend. When this field"
" is set to `true`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:105
msgid ""
"For the Wasm and `wasm-gc` backends, a standalone WebAssembly module will"
" be generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:106
msgid "For the `js` backend, a standalone JavaScript file will be generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:112
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"is-main\": true,\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:121
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"is-main\": true\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:129
msgid "Importing dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:131
msgid "Import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:133
msgid ""
"The `import` field is used to specify other packages that a package "
"depends on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:135
msgid ""
"For example, the following imports `pkgA` and `pkgC`, aliasing `pkgC` to "
"`c`. User can write `@c` to access definitions from `pkgC`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:147
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"import\": [\n"
"        \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgA\",\n"
"        {\n"
"            \"path\": \"moonbit-community/language/packages/pkgC\",\n"
"            \"alias\": \"c\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"moonbitlang/core/builtin\"\n"
"    ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:154
msgid ""
"Most core packages are not special here: if you use `@json`, `@test`, or "
"other ordinary core aliases, add the corresponding `moonbitlang/core/...`"
" package to `import` to avoid `core_package_not_imported` warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:158
msgid ""
"`prelude` is the exception. It is available by default, so the names it "
"exposes do not need an explicit package import."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:161
msgid "Test import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:163
msgid ""
"The test import is used to specify other packages that the black-box test"
" package of this package depends on, with the same format as `import`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:168
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"  \"path/to/package2\" @pkg2,\n"
"} for \"test\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:176
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"test-import\": {\n"
"    \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"path\": \"path/to/package2\",\n"
"      \"alias\": \"pkg2\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:190
msgid ""
"The `test-import-all` field is used to specify whether all public "
"definitions from the package being tested should be imported (`true`) by "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:192
msgid "White-box test import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:194
msgid ""
"The white-box test import is used to specify other packages that the "
"white-box test package of this package depends on, with the same format "
"as `import`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:199
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"  \"path/to/package2\" @pkg2,\n"
"} for \"wbtest\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:207
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"wbtest-import\": {\n"
"    \"path/to/package1\",\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"path\": \"path/to/package2\",\n"
"      \"alias\": \"pkg2\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:221
msgid "Maximum Concurrent Tests"
msgstr "最大同時テスト数"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:223
msgid ""
"The `max-concurrent-tests` field limits how many tests from this package "
"may run at the same time when `moon test` executes the package."
msgstr ""
"`max-concurrent-tests` フィールドは、`moon test` "
"がこのパッケージを実行するときに、このパッケージのテストを同時に実行できる数を制限します。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:226
msgid ""
"This is useful when tests in the same package share ports, temporary "
"files, or other external resources that should not all run in parallel."
msgstr "同じパッケージ内のテストがポート、一時ファイル、または同時実行すべきでないその他の外部リソースを共有する場合に便利です。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:231
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"max-concurrent-tests\": 2,\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:238
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"max-concurrent-tests\": 2\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:246
msgid "Conditional Compilation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:248
msgid "The smallest unit of conditional compilation is a file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:250
msgid ""
"In a conditional compilation expression, three logical operators are "
"supported: `and`, `or`, and `not`, where the `or` operator can be "
"omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:252
msgid ""
"For example, `[\"or\", \"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"]` can be simplified to "
"`[\"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:254
msgid ""
"Conditions in the expression can be categorized into backends and "
"optimization levels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:256
msgid "**Backend conditions**: `\"wasm\"`, `\"wasm-gc\"`, and `\"js\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:257
msgid "**Optimization level conditions**: `\"debug\"` and `\"release\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:259
msgid "Conditional expressions support nesting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:261
msgid ""
"If a file is not listed in `\"targets\"`, it will be compiled under all "
"conditions by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:267
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  targets: {\n"
"    \"only_js.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm_gc.mbt\": [\"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"all_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"not_js.mbt\": [\"not\", \"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_debug.mbt\": [\"debug\"],\n"
"    \"js_and_release.mbt\": [\"and\", [\"js\"], [\"release\"]],\n"
"    \"js_only_test.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"js_or_wasm.mbt\": [\"js\", \"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"wasm_release_or_js_debug.mbt\": [\"or\", [\"and\", \"wasm\", "
"\"release\"], [\"and\", \"js\", \"debug\"]]\n"
"  }\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:286
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"targets\": {\n"
"    \"only_js.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"only_wasm_gc.mbt\": [\"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"all_wasm.mbt\": [\"wasm\", \"wasm-gc\"],\n"
"    \"not_js.mbt\": [\"not\", \"js\"],\n"
"    \"only_debug.mbt\": [\"debug\"],\n"
"    \"js_and_release.mbt\": [\"and\", [\"js\"], [\"release\"]],\n"
"    \"js_only_test.mbt\": [\"js\"],\n"
"    \"js_or_wasm.mbt\": [\"js\", \"wasm\"],\n"
"    \"wasm_release_or_js_debug.mbt\": [\"or\", [\"and\", \"wasm\", "
"\"release\"], [\"and\", \"js\", \"debug\"]]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:305
msgid "Supported Targets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:307
msgid ""
"The `supported-targets` option declares which backends a package is "
"intended to support. It uses a target-set expression, not an array:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:312
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"supported-targets\": \"js\",\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:319
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"supported-targets\": \"js\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:327
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:329
msgid "`js` for a single backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:330
msgid "`+js+wasm-gc` for an explicit set of backends"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:331
msgid "`+all-js` for all backends except `js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:333
msgid "Legacy array syntax is still accepted for compatibility:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:335
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"supported-targets\": [\"js\", \"native\"]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:341
msgid "This is package metadata, not a conditional compilation rule:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:343
msgid "use `supported-targets` to declare the package's supported backend set"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:344
msgid ""
"use `targets` to include or exclude individual files for different "
"backends"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:345
msgid ""
"use `preferred-target` in `moon.mod.json` to choose the default backend "
"for commands such as `moon check`, `moon run`, and `moon build`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:347
msgid ""
"When both the module and the package declare `supported-targets`, the "
"effective backend set is their intersection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:350
msgid "Command behavior follows the selected backend:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:352
msgid ""
"`moon check`, `moon build`, `moon test`, and `moon bench` keep only "
"packages that support the selected backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:353
msgid "`moon run` requires the selected package to support the selected backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:354
msgid "`moon info` skips unsupported selected packages with a warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:355
msgid ""
"`moon bundle` skips package targets that do not support the selected "
"backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:357
msgid ""
"After root selection, Moon also checks reachable required dependencies. "
"If a required dependency does not support the selected backend, the "
"command fails with a normal user-facing error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:360
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:362
msgid "omitting `supported-targets` means all backends are supported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:363
msgid ""
"`--target all` expands to `wasm`, `wasm-gc`, `js`, and `native`, but not "
"`llvm`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:364
msgid "`llvm` is still a valid `supported-targets` value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:365
msgid "legacy array syntax is deprecated, but still accepted for compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:367
msgid "A common setup is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:369
msgid "mark a native-only package with `\"supported-targets\": \"native\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:370
msgid "set `\"preferred-target\": \"native\"` in `moon.mod.json`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:371
msgid "use `targets` only when some files inside the package differ by backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:373
msgid "Native Stub Files"
msgstr "ネイティブスタブファイル"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:375
msgid ""
"The `native-stub` field lists C stub source files that should be compiled"
" with this package for native builds."
msgstr "`native-stub` フィールドは、native ビルド向けにこのパッケージと一緒にコンパイルすべき C スタブソースファイルを列挙します。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:378
msgid ""
"This is commonly used together with [`extern \"C\"` declarations in the "
"FFI documentation](../../language/ffi.md), where the stub file provides "
"wrapper functions or adapter code that is easier to write in C than "
"directly in MoonBit."
msgstr ""
"これは、[FFI ドキュメントにある `extern \"C\"` 宣言](../../language/ffi.md) "
"と組み合わせて使われることが多く、その場合スタブファイルは、MoonBit で直接書くより C "
"で書く方が容易なラッパー関数やアダプタコードを提供します。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:383
msgid "Paths are relative to the package directory."
msgstr "パスはパッケージディレクトリからの相対パスです。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:387
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  \"native-stub\": [ \"stub.c\", \"helpers.c\" ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:394
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"native-stub\": [\"stub.c\", \"helpers.c\"]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:402
msgid "Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:404
msgid ""
"By default, moon only links packages where `is-main` is set to `true`. If"
" you need to link other packages, you can specify this with the `link` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:406
msgid ""
"The `link` option is used to specify link options, and its value can be "
"either a boolean or an object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:408
msgid ""
"Currently, `link` does not work for the native backend. The behavior "
"described in this section applies to the `wasm`, `wasm-gc`, and `js` "
"backends."
msgstr ""
"現在、`link` は native バックエンドでは動作しません。この節で説明する挙動は `wasm`、`wasm-gc`、`js` "
"バックエンドに適用されます。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:411
msgid ""
"When the `link` value is `true`, it indicates that the package should be "
"linked. The output will vary depending on the backend specified during "
"the build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:415
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: true\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:422
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": true\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:430
msgid ""
"When the `link` value is an object, it indicates that the package should "
"be linked, and you can specify link options. For detailed configuration, "
"please refer to the subpage for the corresponding backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:432
msgid "Wasm Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:434
msgid "Common Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:436
msgid ""
"The `exports` option is used to specify the function names exported by "
"the Wasm backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:438
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, the `hello` function from "
"the current package is exported as the `hello` function in the Wasm "
"module, and the `foo` function is exported as the `bar` function in the "
"Wasm module. In the Wasm host, the `hello` and `bar` functions can be "
"called to invoke the `hello` and `foo` functions from the current "
"package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:442
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [ \"hello\", \"foo:bar\" ],\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [ \"hello\", \"foo:bar\" ],\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:456
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [\n"
"        \"hello\",\n"
"        \"foo:bar\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [\n"
"        \"hello\",\n"
"        \"foo:bar\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:477
msgid ""
"The `import-memory` option is used to specify the linear memory imported "
"by the Wasm module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:479
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration specifies that the linear memory"
" imported by the Wasm module is the `memory` variable from the `env` "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:483
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\",\n"
"      },\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\",\n"
"      },\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:503
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"import-memory\": {\n"
"        \"module\": \"env\",\n"
"        \"name\": \"memory\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:524
msgid ""
"The `memory-limits` option is used to specify the minimum and maximum "
"size of the linear memory used by the Wasm module."
msgstr "`memory-limits` オプションは、Wasm モジュールが使用する線形メモリの最小サイズと最大サイズを指定するために使います。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:527
msgid "The `shared-memory` option is used to enable shared linear memory."
msgstr "`shared-memory` オプションは、共有線形メモリを有効にするために使います。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:529
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration sets memory limits and enables "
"shared memory for both the `wasm` and `wasm-gc` backends."
msgstr "たとえば、次の設定では `wasm` と `wasm-gc` の両バックエンドに対してメモリ制限を設定し、共有メモリを有効にしています。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:534
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"memory-limits\": {\n"
"        \"min\": 1,\n"
"        \"max\": 65536,\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"shared-memory\": true,\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"memory-limits\": {\n"
"        \"min\": 1,\n"
"        \"max\": 65535,\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"shared-memory\": true,\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:556
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"memory-limits\": {\n"
"        \"min\": 1,\n"
"        \"max\": 65536\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"shared-memory\": true\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"memory-limits\": {\n"
"        \"min\": 1,\n"
"        \"max\": 65535\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"shared-memory\": true\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:579
msgid ""
"The `export-memory-name` option is used to specify the name of the linear"
" memory exported by the Wasm module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:583
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\",\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:597
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"export-memory-name\": \"memory\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:612
msgid "Wasm Linear Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:614
msgid ""
"The `heap-start-address` option is used to specify the starting address "
"of the linear memory that can be used when compiling to the Wasm backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:616
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration sets the starting address of the"
" linear memory to 1024."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:620
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"heap-start-address\": 1024,\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:631
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm\": {\n"
"      \"heap-start-address\": 1024\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:643
msgid "Wasm GC Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:645
msgid ""
"The `use-js-builtin-string` option is used to specify whether the [JS "
"String Builtin Proposal](https://github.com/WebAssembly/js-string-"
"builtins/blob/main/proposals/js-string-builtins/Overview.md) should be "
"enabled when compiling to the Wasm GC backend. It will make the `String` "
"in MoonBit equivalent to the `String` in JavaScript host runtime."
msgstr ""
"`use-js-builtin-string` オプションは、Wasm GC バックエンドへコンパイルする際に [JS String "
"Builtin Proposal](https://github.com/WebAssembly/js-string-"
"builtins/blob/main/proposals/js-string-builtins/Overview.md) "
"を有効にするかどうかを指定します。これにより、MoonBit の `String` は JavaScript ホストランタイムの `String`"
" と等価になります。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:648
msgid "For example, the following configuration enables the JS String Builtin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:652
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true,\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:663
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:675
msgid ""
"The `imported-string-constants` option is used to specify the imported "
"string namespace used by the JS String Builtin Proposal, which is \"_\" "
"by default. It should meet the configuration in the JS host runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:678
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration and JS initialization configures"
" the imported string namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:682
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true,\n"
"      \"imported-string-constants\": \"_\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:694
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"wasm-gc\": {\n"
"      \"use-js-builtin-string\": true,\n"
"      \"imported-string-constants\": \"_\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:707
msgid ""
"const { instance } = await WebAssembly.instantiate(bytes, {}, { "
"importedStringConstants: \"strings\" });\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:711
msgid "JS Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:713
msgid ""
"The `exports` option is used to specify the function names to export in "
"the JavaScript module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:715
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, the `hello` function from "
"the current package is exported as the `hello` function in the JavaScript"
" module. In the JavaScript host, the `hello` function can be called to "
"invoke the `hello` function from the current package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:719
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [ \"hello\" ],\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:730
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"exports\": [\n"
"        \"hello\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:744
msgid ""
"The `format` option is used to specify the output format of the "
"JavaScript module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:746
msgid "The currently supported formats are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:747
msgid "`esm` (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:748
msgid "`cjs`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:749
msgid "`iife`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:751
msgid ""
"For example, the following configuration sets the output format of the "
"current package to ES Module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:755
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"format\": \"esm\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:766
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"js\": {\n"
"      \"format\": \"esm\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:778
msgid "Native Backend Link Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:780
msgid ""
"The `cc` option is used to specify the compiler for compiling the "
"`moonc`-generated C source files. It can be either a full path to the "
"compiler or a simple name that is accessible via the PATH environment "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:785
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc\": \"/usr/bin/gcc13\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:796
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc\": \"/usr/bin/gcc13\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:808
msgid ""
"The `cc-flags` option is used to override the default flags passed to the"
" compiler. For example, you can use the following flag to define a macro "
"called MOONBIT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:813
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-flags\": \"-DMOONBIT\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:824
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-flags\": \"-DMOONBIT\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:836
msgid ""
"The `cc-link-flags` option is used to override the default flags passed "
"to the linker. Since the linker is invoked through the compiler driver "
"(e.g., `cc` instead of `ld`, `cl` instead of `link`), you should prefix "
"specific options with `-Wl,` or `/link ` when passing them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:840
msgid "The following example strips symbol information from produced binary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:844
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  link: {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-link-flags\": \"-s\",\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:855
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"link\": {\n"
"    \"native\": {\n"
"      \"cc-link-flags\": \"-s\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:867
msgid ""
"The `stub-cc` option is similar to `cc` but controls which compiler to "
"use for compiling stubs. Although it can be different from `cc`, it is "
"not recommended and should only be used for debugging purposes. "
"Therefore, we strongly recommend to specify `cc` and `stub-cc` at the "
"same time and make them consistent to avoid potential conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:872
msgid ""
"The `stub-cc-flags` is similar to `cc-flags`. It only have effects on "
"stubs compilation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:874
msgid ""
"The `stub-cc-link-flags` are similar but have a subtle difference.  "
"Normally, stubs are compiled into object files and linked against object "
"files generated from `moonc`-generated C source files.  This linking is "
"only controlled by `cc-flags` and `cc-link-flags`, as mentioned earlier."
"  However, in specific modes, such as when the fast-debugging-test "
"feature is enabled, there will be a separate linking procedure for stub "
"objects files, where  `stub-cc-link-flags` will take effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:881
msgid "Default C compiler and compiler flags for the native backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:883
msgid ""
"Here is a brief summarization to "
"[compiler_flags.rs](https://github.com/moonbitlang/moon/blob/main/crates/moonutil/src/compiler_flags.rs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:885
msgid "C Compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:887
msgid "Search in PATH for the following items from top to bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:889
msgid "cl"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:890
msgid "gcc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:891
msgid "clang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:892
msgid "cc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:893
msgid "the internal tcc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:895
msgid ""
"For GCC-like compilers, the default compile & link command is as follows."
" `[]` is used to indicate the flags may not exist in some modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:897
msgid ""
"cc -o $target -I$MOON_HOME/include -L$MOON_HOME/lib [-g] [-shared -fPIC] "
"\\\n"
"   -fwrapv -fno-strict-aliasing (-O2|-Og) "
"[$MOON_HOME/lib/libmoonbitrun.o] \\\n"
"   $sources -lm $cc_flags $cc_link_flags\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:903
