"cl (/Fo|/Fe)$target -I$MOON_HOME/include [/LD] /utf-8 /wd4819 /nologo "
"(/O2|/Od) \\\n"
"   /link /LIBPATH:$MOON_HOME/lib\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:909
msgid "Rule and dev_build"
msgstr "rule と dev_build"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:911
msgid ""
"`rule` declares a reusable command, and `dev_build` applies a rule to "
"concrete input and output files. These pre-build steps run before "
"development commands such as `moon check`, `moon build`, and `moon test`."
msgstr ""
"`rule` は再利用可能なコマンドを宣言し、`dev_build` は具体的な入力ファイルと出力ファイルに `rule` を適用します。"
"これらの事前ビルドステップは、`moon check`、`moon build`、`moon test` などの開発用コマンドの前に実行されます。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:915
msgid ""
"This mechanism is intended for package authors during package "
"development. When the package is used as a dependency by downstream "
"users, these pre-build steps are not triggered for security reasons, so "
"dependencies do not execute arbitrary commands during builds. Commit the "
"generated output files to the repository so downstream users can build "
"against them directly."
msgstr ""
"この仕組みは、パッケージ作者がパッケージ開発中に使用することを想定しています。"
"そのパッケージが下流ユーザーの依存関係として使われる場合、セキュリティ上の理由から、これらの事前ビルドステップは実行されません。"
"そのため、依存関係がビルド中に任意のコマンドを実行することはありません。生成された出力ファイルをリポジトリにコミットし、"
"下流ユーザーがそれらを直接使ってビルドできるようにしてください。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:921
msgid ""
"`rule(name: \"...\", command: \"...\")` declares a reusable command "
"template. The `name` field identifies the rule, and `command` is a shell "
"command string. The command can refer to `$input` and `$output`, which "
"are supplied by the `dev_build` entry that uses the rule. A package can "
"declare multiple `rule` entries."
msgstr ""
"`rule(name: \"...\", command: \"...\")` は再利用可能なコマンドテンプレートを宣言します。"
"`name` フィールドはその `rule` を識別し、`command` はシェルコマンド文字列です。"
"コマンドは `$input` と `$output` を参照できます。これらは、その `rule` を使用する `dev_build` エントリから提供されます。"
"パッケージは複数の `rule` エントリを宣言できます。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:927
msgid ""
"`dev_build(rule: \"...\", input: \"...\", output: \"...\")` declares a "
"pre-build step. It selects a rule and supplies the input and output paths"
" used when expanding that rule's command. A package can declare multiple "
"`dev_build` entries."
msgstr ""
"`dev_build(rule: \"...\", input: \"...\", output: \"...\")` は事前ビルドステップを宣言します。"
"これは `rule` を選択し、その `rule` のコマンドを展開するときに使用する入力パスと出力パスを提供します。"
"パッケージは複数の `dev_build` エントリを宣言できます。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:932
msgid ""
"Rules can be declared either as package-level rules in the same "
"`moon.pkg` or as module-level rules in "
"[`moon.mod`](/toolchain/moon/module.md). A package-level rule is visible "
"only to `dev_build` entries in that same `moon.pkg`; a module-level rule "
"is visible to `dev_build` entries in every package in the module. When "
"resolving a rule name, `moon` first looks for a package-level rule in the"
" same `moon.pkg`, then for a module-level rule in `moon.mod`."
msgstr ""
"`rule` は、同じ `moon.pkg` 内のパッケージレベル `rule` として宣言することも、"
"[`moon.mod`](/toolchain/moon/module.md) 内のモジュールレベル `rule` として宣言することもできます。"
"パッケージレベル `rule` は、同じ `moon.pkg` 内の `dev_build` エントリからのみ参照できます。"
"モジュールレベル `rule` は、モジュール内のすべてのパッケージの `dev_build` エントリから参照できます。"
"`rule` 名を解決するとき、`moon` はまず同じ `moon.pkg` 内のパッケージレベル `rule` を探し、"
"次に `moon.mod` 内のモジュールレベル `rule` を探します。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:941
msgid ""
"rule(name: \"copy\", command: \"cat $input > $output\")\n"
"dev_build(rule: \"copy\", input: \"a.txt\", output: \"a.mbt\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:947
msgid ""
"The `rule` and `dev_build` entries are not supported in `moon.pkg.json`. "
"Use the deprecated `pre-build` configuration instead:"
msgstr ""
"`moon.pkg.json` では `rule` エントリと `dev_build` エントリはサポートされていません。"
"代わりに、非推奨の `pre-build` 設定を使用してください："

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:949
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"pre-build\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"input\": \"a.txt\",\n"
"      \"output\": \"a.mbt\",\n"
"      \"command\": \"cat $input > $output\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:963
msgid ""
"In this example, running a development command such as `moon check` "
"copies the contents of `a.txt` to `a.mbt` before the package is checked."
msgstr ""
"この例では、`moon check` などの開発用コマンドを実行すると、パッケージがチェックされる前に `a.txt` の内容が `a.mbt` にコピーされます。"

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:966
msgid "Warnings List"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:968
msgid ""
"Used to disable warnings, enable warnings, or treat a warning as a fatal "
"error. The warning list is a string composed of multiple warning name, "
"each prefixed with a sign:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:971
msgid "`-` to disable the warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:972
msgid "`+` to enable the warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:973
msgid "`@` to treat the enabled warning as a fatal error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:975
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, `-unused_value` disables the"
" unused functions and variables warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:979
msgid "warnings = \"-unused_value\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:984
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"-unused_value\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:992
msgid ""
"If multiple warnings need to be disabled, they can be directly connected "
"and combined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:996
msgid "warnings = \"-unused_value-unreachable_code\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1001
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"-unused_value-unreachable_code\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1009
msgid ""
"If it is necessary to activate certain warnings that were originally "
"prohibited, use the plus sign."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1013
msgid "warnings = \"+unused_optional_argument\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1018
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"+unused_optional_argument\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1026
msgid "To treat a warning as a fatal error, use the `@`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1030
msgid "warnings = \"@deprecated\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1035
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"@deprecated\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1043
msgid ""
"You can also use warning numbers in `warn-list`. In the output below, "
"`mnemonic` is the symbolic warning name used in warning lists, while `id`"
" is the numeric form of the same warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1047
msgid "The current list from `moonc check -warn-help` is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1049
msgid ""
"Available warnings:\n"
"mnemonic                   description"
"                                                     id state\n"
"unused_value               Unused variable or function."
"                                     1 warn\n"
"unused_value               Unused variable."
"                                                 2 warn\n"
"unused_type_declaration    Unused type declaration."
"                                         3 warn\n"
"missing_priv               Unused abstract type."
"                                            4 warn\n"
"unused_type_variable       Unused type variable."
"                                            5 warn\n"
"unused_constructor         Unused constructor."
"                                              6 warn\n"
"unused_field               Unused field or constructor argument."
"                            7 warn\n"
"redundant_modifier         Redundant modifier."
"                                              8 warn\n"
"struct_never_constructed   Struct never constructed."
"                                        9 warn\n"
"unused_pattern             Unused pattern."
"                                                 10 warn\n"
"partial_match              Partial pattern matching."
"                                       11 error\n"
"unreachable_code           Unreachable code."
"                                               12 warn\n"
"unresolved_type_variable   Unresolved type variable."
"                                       13 warn\n"
"alert or alert_<category>  All alerts or alerts with specific category."
"                    14 warn\n"
"unused_mut                 Unused mutability."
"                                              15 error\n"
"parser_inconsistency       Parser inconsistency check."
"                                     16 warn\n"
"ambiguous_loop_argument    Ambiguous usage of loop argument."
"                               17 warn\n"
"useless_loop               Useless loop expression."
"                                        18 warn\n"
"deprecated                 Deprecated API usage."
