#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1128
msgid "Use `moonc check -warn-help` to see the list of preset compiler warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1131
msgid "Alert Warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1133
msgid ""
"Alerts are special warnings that indicate the usage of API marked with  "
"[`#internal` attribute](../../language/attributes.md#internal-attribute)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1136
msgid ""
"All alerts has a category associated with it, which is customized by the "
"author of the API. You can enable or disable specific alert categories "
"using the `alert_<category>` warning name, or use `alert` to control all "
"alert warnings at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1140
msgid ""
"For example, in the following configuration, all warnings for alerts are "
"treated  as fatal errors, except for the `unsafe` category, which is "
"disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1145
msgid "warnings = \"@alert-alert_unsafe\" \n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1150
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"warn-list\": \"@alert-alert_unsafe\" \n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1158
msgid "Virtual Package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1160
msgid ""
"A virtual package serves as an interface of a package that can be "
"replaced by actual implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1162
msgid "Declarations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1164
msgid ""
"The `virtual` field is used to declare the current package as a virtual "
"package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1166
msgid ""
"For example, the following declares a virtual package with default "
"implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1170
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  virtual: {\n"
"    \"has-default\": true,\n"
"  },\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1179
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"virtual\": {\n"
"    \"has-default\": true\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1189
msgid "Implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1191
msgid ""
"The `implement` field is used to declare the virtual package to be "
"implemented by the current package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1193
msgid "For example, the following implements a virtual package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1197
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  implement: \"moonbitlang/core/abort\",\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1204
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"implement\": \"moonbitlang/core/abort\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1212
msgid "Overriding implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1214
msgid ""
"The `overrides` field is used to provide the implementations that "
"fulfills an imported virtual package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1216
msgid ""
"For example, the following overrides the default implementation of the "
"builtin abort package with another package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1220
msgid ""
"options(\n"
"  overrides: [ \"moonbitlang/dummy_abort/abort_show_msg\" ],\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package.md:1227
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"overrides\": [\"moonbitlang/dummy_abort/abort_show_msg\"]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

